fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">horted him to turn from his iniquity, that the Lord </div><div class="t m6d0 x11 h2d y1676 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">might repent him of the evil. He warned Judah </div><div class="t ma60 x11 h2d y188a ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">that because of their sins God would bring against </div><div class="t m175 x11 h2d yc28 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">them the king of Babylon, who would lay waste </div><div class="t m1116 x11 h2d y1851 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Jerusalem. Because of this the king sought to </div><div class="t m835 x11 h2d y1fd ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">slay Jeremiah. See Jer. 22 : 13-19; 26:1-15, and </div><div class="t m44 x11 h2d yb9f ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">elsewhere. </div><div class="t m157f x73 h2d y188b ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">5.&apos; Who saved Jeremiah from death? Jer. 26: </div><div class="t m374 x17 h2d y188c ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">24. </div><div class="t m1d0 x73 h2d y1773 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">6. </div><div class="t m5e4 xc h2d y6b2 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">How was Jehoiakim&apos;s subjection to Babylon </div><div class="t m308 x17 h2d y2c6 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">fulfilled? </div><div class="t mf02 x3f h3b y2c6 ff6 fs16 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Ans.—By </div><div class="t m449 x6b h2d y2c6 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">the overthrow of Egypt, Ju-</div><div class="t m3b5 x11 h2d y5dc ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">dah&apos;s support. See Jer. 46:2, 13; 2 Kings 24:1. </div><div class="t m1d2 x73 h2d yc65 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">7. </div><div class="t m6c8 xc h2d yc65 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">What instruction did God give Jeremiah </div><div class="t m424 x17 h2d y6b6 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">with reference to a repetition of these solemn warn- </div><div class="t m1291 x17 h2d yc66 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">ings? Jer. </div><div class="t m5 x3f h2d y6b8 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"></div><div class="t me8e x40 h2d y6b8 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">2. </div><div class="t m1d5 x74 h2d y6b9 ff4 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">8. </div><div class="t m653 xc5 h2d y6b9 f